sookie
Homonym Number: 1
Word Class:noun
Sense Number:2
Definition:transf to a person, espec. a child, who behaves like a calf; a crybaby; a sissy
Origin:
Register:
Register 2:
Domain:[none]
Region:[none]
See:
Pronunciation:
Notes: ca1920 R. Mason's mother
